 Holding General Secretary Kim Jong Il, distinguished statesman and iron-willed brilliant commander, in high esteem, the DPRK has won one victory after another, meeting the challenges of the imperialists and weathering out all sorts of trials and greeted a new heyday of building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation, it noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that only victory and glory are in store for the Korean people struggling to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country and open up the gate of a great prosperous powerful nation under the outstanding Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, the statement extended full support and solidarity to the Korean people in their just cause.

Birthday of DPRK Observed in Brazil and Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 13 (KCNA) -- The Brazilian and Nigerian organizations issued bulletins to mark the 60th anniversary of the foundation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Brazil-Korea Friendship Association carried an article titled "2008, year of historic turn in the DPRK" in its bulletin on Sept. 2. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article said that President Kim Il Sung's founding of the DPRK marked a historic event in which he put forward the Korean people as an independent and powerful revolutionary people and ushered in a new era of building a socialist state centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article noted that the cause of building a rich and powerful country of Kim Il Sung, father of socialist Korea and father of the nation-building, is being successfully carried forward by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pointing out that the Korean people would greet the centenary of birth of Kim Il Sung in 2012, the article stressed that it is the resolution and will of the Workers' Party of Korea to fling open the gate of a great prosperous powerful nation in 2012 without fail by bringing economy and the standard of people's living to a high level in reliance upon the tremendous political and military potentials reinforced by dint of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Nigerian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea said in an article titled "Warm congratulations on the 60th birthday of the DPRK" carried in its bulletin on Sept. 3 that the President expounded an original idea and theory of nation-building, thus providing firm guidelines for nation-building, built a genuine people's government and developed it into a powerful weapon for carrying out the cause of socialism and built the DPRK into a country winning one victory after another in reliance upon the solid political, military and economic foundations.

